raw_data.title: Data Analyst I
raw_data.description: Under general direction, verifies and maintains accurate data in the master and control files of a data base in a user environment. Identifies, researches and analyzes data errors or inconsistencies within a data base system. Determines appropriate corrective actions. May discuss problems and solutions with data base users. Updates master and control files as needed. Generates and reviews system reports. Responds to requests for reports or information. Maintains documentation on system files and reports. May recommend data base improvements or coordinate system modifications with the appropriate personnel.

raw_data.title: Data Analyst II
raw_data.description: Under minimal direction, creates design of data tables in the master and control files of a database in a user environment. Analyzes data requirements of business and develops strategies to eliminate inconsistencies within a database system. Recommends business solutions based on customer requirements and industry trends. Leads, plans, schedules, and controls complex projects and activities with customers, support groups, and vendors on concurrent projects. Applies extensive knowledge of the customer's business and industry to develop project specifications. Leads the training of customers and peers.

raw_data.title: Database Administrator
raw_data.description: Under minimal direction, In addition to Database Administrator I related functions manages the development of database projects. Provides daily supervision and direction to support staff. Performs database backup, restore, granting of user rights and performance improvement tasks. Reviews system and programming designs to ensure efficient use of database resources.

raw_data.title: ERP Consultant
raw_data.description: Working under minimal supervision, performs evaluation, customizations and implementation tasks for Enterprise Resource Planning (ERP) software using broad industry experience, including industry best practices and extensive ERP software knowledge. Leads parts of the project and creates project methodology as needed. Provides knowledge of multiple functional areas or other areas of expertise* with hands-on experience in multiple ERP software modules and has the ability to transfer knowledge and skill. Accomplished at several professional level roles, both functional and technical, and knowledgeable about applying technology to business operations in multiple industries. Applies industry best practices, ERP software knowledge, and experience to lead overall business requirements gathering sessions and makes overall business process recommendations. Develops or executes functional and technical specifications, modifications, enhancements and testing for complex interfaces, module integration, system extensions, and reporting systems. Executes project plan tasks and other duties as assigned. Provides regular status on tasks and issues. Coordinates resources and occasionally assumes project management responsibilities.

raw_data.title: Help Desk Specialist
raw_data.description: Serves as the initial point-of-contact for troubleshooting hardware/software, PC, and printer problems. Provides phone and in-person support to users in the areas of e-mail, directories, standard Windows desktop applications, and applications developed under current contract or predecessors.

raw_data.title: Programmer Analyst I
raw_data.description: Under immediate direction, performs assigned portions of design, programming, and documentation for all IT or ADP systems. Participates in assigned phases of software development with emphasis on the programming, testing acceptance phases. Supports the preparation of technical reports and related documentation. Responsible for specific aspects of assigned projects.

raw_data.title: Programmer Analyst II
raw_data.description: Under general direction, performs assigned portions of design, programming, and documentation for all IT or ADP systems. Participates in assigned phases of software development with emphasis on the programming, testing acceptance phases. Supports the preparation of technical reports and related documentation. Responsible for specific aspects of assigned projects.

raw_data.title: Programmer Analyst III
raw_data.description: Under limited direction, performs assigned portions of design, programming, and documentation for all IT or ADP systems. Participates in assigned phases of software development with emphasis on the programming, testing acceptance phases. Supports the preparation of technical reports and related documentation. Responsible for specific aspects of assigned projects. Handles more complex coding and development tasks.

raw_data.title: Programmer Analyst IV
raw_data.description: Under minimal direction, performs assigned portions of design, programming, and documentation for all IT or ADP systems. Participates in assigned phases of software development with emphasis on the programming, testing acceptance phases. Prepares technical reports and related documentation. May be responsible for completion of a phase of a project. Provides guidance and training to less experienced programmers. Reviews code and helps junior programmer in the team

labor_categories.labor_category: IT Project Manager I (Project Lead I)

raw_data.title: IT Project Manager I (Project Lead I)
raw_data.description: Responsible for coordinating, defining, staffing, and managing one or multiple projects. Works across the business, management, Quality Assurance and Testing, Systems Analyst, Software Development, and Technical Writing teams to ensure the delivery of a high quality software application. Primary technical point of contact with higher-level Project Manager(s) and/or Program Manager and various technical personnel on project. Develops project schedules, coordinates project status meetings, manages resources in all phases of software development lifecycle. Works with the project business owner to oversee delivery performance, ensure delivery quality and report schedule, cost, and execution performance.

labor_categories.labor_category: IT Project Manager II (Project Lead II)

raw_data.title: IT Project Manager II (Project Lead II)
raw_data.description: Directs the performance of a variety of highly technical projects which may be organized by technology, program or client. Oversees the technology development and/or application, and resource allocation within program client base. Project areas typically include engineering, integration, test, systems analysis, quality assurance, etc. Responsible for the quality and timely delivery of all contractual items. Operates within client guidance, contractual limitations, and Company business and policy directives. Serves as focal point of contact with client regarding program activities. Ensures that all required resources are available for program implementation. Maintains the development and execution of business opportunities based on broad, general guidance. Confers with junior project manager to provide technical advice and to assist with problem resolution.

raw_data.title: Quality Assurance Analyst
raw_data.description: Under limited direction, involved within the Software Development Lifecycle to test software applications and ensure that they meet specifications. Involved in design, development and execution of test cases, test reports, test plans, test schedules and procedures. Gathers and analyzes quality statistics and documents findings for management.

raw_data.title: Systems Analyst
raw_data.description: Experienced in identifying and assessing requirements for new or modified information systems Performs detailed systems analysis, interprets written specifications, and conducts module and integration testing. Performs analysis of computer systems.

raw_data.title: Senior Consultant/Architect
raw_data.description: Responsible for all or part of the systems and/or business intelligence architecture, analysis and/or design. Responsibilities may include object modelling, performance, database/architecture design, operation and maintenance, availability, sustainability and stability of the system/architecture etc.

raw_data.title: IT Technical Writer
raw_data.description: Independently prepares various system documentation, user manuals, help menus, installation guides that includes text material as well as flow charts and diagrams to convey the technical information in simple English. Interacts with users and subject matter experts to gather the documentation requirements and incorporate them in the respective technical and user documentation
